{
  "doc_id": "60572",
  "text": "These POL/PLL1-interacting lipids are known to play important roles in regulating cellular functions. PI(3)P is required for vesicle trafficking particularly between the trans-Golgi network and the vacuole [CITATION_1] . PI(4)P is involved in a number of processes, including regulating root hair polarity and trafficking between the trans-Golgi network and the plasma membrane [CITATION_2] . PI(5)P binds to and negatively regulates the Arabidopsis histone methyltransferase, ARABIDOPSIS TRI-THORAX1 (ATX1), which results in an alteration of the expression of ATX1-controlled genes ( [CITATION_3] . PS is a cofactor for a number of enzymes, such as protein kinase C, and can also activate various proteins, including the Na + /K + ATPase [CITATION_4] .",
